talkin', talkin' like he kept
drummin', drummin', drummin'!

1012
01:07:23,830 --> 01:07:25,830
What are you trying
to do, Mr. bower?

1013
01:07:25,840 --> 01:07:27,845
Get Alice fired
before she starts?

1014
01:07:27,846 --> 01:07:30,839
Oh, hold on...
moving in,
taking over a school.

1015
01:07:30,840 --> 01:07:34,340
I didn't exactly take over.
I asked you to send
the children home,

1016
01:07:34,350 --> 01:07:36,349
to tell them
there wouldn't be
any school today.

1017
01:07:36,350 --> 01:07:38,855
Now, Joe...
the young'uns
were already there.

1018
01:07:38,856 --> 01:07:41,830
Most of them
was all gussied up,
bein' the first day of school.

1019
01:07:41,840 --> 01:07:44,809
It just seemed a shame
to send them home.

1020
01:07:44,810 --> 01:07:48,309
I don't think he meant any harm.

1021
01:07:48,310 --> 01:07:51,809
Right while you and I were
meeting with the school board,
giving our word of honor...

1022
01:07:51,810 --> 01:07:55,310
<i>That nothing like this
would ever happen!
It won't ever happen again.</i>

1023
01:07:55,820 --> 01:07:59,325
I figured if Alice knowed
enough to teach them
for a whole year,

1024
01:07:59,326 --> 01:08:02,319
I knowed enough
to teach them for one day;
Just part of a day, actually.

1025
01:08:02,320 --> 01:08:05,820
But that's just the point!
You didn't teach them!

1026
01:08:05,830 --> 01:08:07,840
Joe, please!
You got them cornered
in the schoolhouse...

1027
01:08:07,841 --> 01:08:10,329
<i>And then you delivered
a political oration...</i>

1028
01:08:10,330 --> 01:08:13,329
About not dividing Dakota,
about making it one state!

1029
01:08:13,330 --> 01:08:17,839
It oughta be one state!
If you had a lick of brains,
you'd see it for yourself!

1030
01:08:17,840 --> 01:08:21,339
Grandpa, that's enough!

1031
01:08:21,340 --> 01:08:24,840
I'm sorry, Mrs. bower.

1032
01:08:26,350 --> 01:08:29,360
Let's just hope none
of the other students
go home and start talking.

1033
01:08:29,361 --> 01:08:32,350
I wouldn't figure on that!

1034
01:08:35,360 --> 01:08:38,870
Joe! Joe.

1035
01:08:40,860 --> 01:08:46,360
After this, if it's anything
to do with my family,
just let me handle it.

1036
01:08:46,370 --> 01:08:50,369
[ Sighs ]

1037
01:08:50,370 --> 01:08:54,370
Look, it isn't just
about your family.

1038
01:08:54,380 --> 01:08:58,879
That's a public school.
I know.

1039
01:08:58,880 --> 01:09:03,379
I also know that you don't
know grandpa the way I do.

1040
01:09:03,380 --> 01:09:05,880
To you, he's probably just
a cantankerous old man...

1041
01:09:05,890 --> 01:09:09,895
That's not the point!
He might be the sweetest man
in the whole world!

1042
01:09:09,896 --> 01:09:12,389
But if he's gonna
take over a public school,

1043
01:09:12,390 --> 01:09:16,390
inject politics
into the classroom, then...

1044
01:09:16,400 --> 01:09:19,410
Then it's not just
a little thing that
you can patch up at home.

1045
01:09:19,411 --> 01:09:21,400
I'll say one thing for you.

1046
01:09:21,900 --> 01:09:24,900
For a man that goes around
preachin' treason agin our
United States government,

1047
01:09:24,910 --> 01:09:28,915
you sure make a big fuss over
a little thing like me teachin'
school for a couple hours.

1048
01:09:28,916 --> 01:09:30,910
What do you mean
"treason," Mr. bower?

1049
01:09:31,410 --> 01:09:34,050
This business you keep
talkin' about settin' up
your own government,

1050
01:09:34,420 --> 01:09:37,419
defying the president
and the congress that's been
elected by the people!

1051
01:09:37,420 --> 01:09:42,925
Mr. bower, I don't mind you
arguing politics, so long as you
don't do it in a schoolhouse.

1052
01:09:42,926 --> 01:09:46,920
You're entitled to your
own opinion, even if it is
completely ridiculous!

1053
01:09:46,930 --> 01:09:49,940
But when you go around, start
accusing people of treason...

1054
01:09:50,430 --> 01:09:52,930
Joe, stop it!
Grandpa, get back
in that house!

1055
01:09:53,430 --> 01:09:56,430
[ Joe ] I don't care if he is
your grandfather, he's not
gonna accuse me of treason!

1056
01:09:56,440 --> 01:09:59,945
It ain't just my idea.
It's in the <i>Democratic digest!
Grandpa!</i>

1057
01:09:59,946 --> 01:10:02,439
The president himself
may send troops...
be quiet!

1058
01:10:02,440 --> 01:10:07,950
I'm asking you as nicely
as I know how, please leave.

1059
01:10:09,420 --> 01:10:12,419
Alice. Alice.

1060
01:10:12,420 --> 01:10:14,920
No!

1061
01:10:15,420 --> 01:10:17,420
[ Door slams ]

1062
01:10:23,430 --> 01:10:25,430
[ Whinnies ]

1063
01:10:41,450 --> 01:10:43,449
Best thing could have
happened for Alice,

1064
01:10:43,450 --> 01:10:45,950
break it off
with a man like that.

1065
01:10:47,460 --> 01:10:51,470
Cause her nothing but heartache
the longer she knowed him.

1066
01:10:54,460 --> 01:10:59,460
I... think it's time
for the two of us...

1067
01:10:59,470 --> 01:11:02,980
<i>To have a little talk.</i>

1068
01:11:20,990 --> 01:11:23,990
In here as good a place as any.

1069
01:11:50,020 --> 01:11:53,030
Remember the last time
I took you to the woodshed?

1070
01:11:53,031 --> 01:11:58,020
When you fought
that barros boy
and bloodied his nose.

1071
01:11:58,030 --> 01:12:03,040
Never forget how you
kept a'wigglin' around.
[ Chuckles ]

1072
01:12:05,030 --> 01:12:07,530
I had me a big
old kindlin' stick,

1073
01:12:07,540 --> 01:12:10,539
but mostly it kept
a'whangin' away in the air,

1074
01:12:10,540 --> 01:12:13,039
never connectin' with nothin'.

1075
01:12:13,040 --> 01:12:16,540
And all the time you was
a'howlin' like a banshee.

1076
01:12:20,050 --> 01:12:22,549
I'm gonna tell you something.

1077
01:12:22,550 --> 01:12:26,050
Most of the time
I was missin' the purpose.

1078
01:12:30,220 --> 01:12:35,729
This isn't gonna be easy.
Just don't know how to say it.

1079
01:12:35,730 --> 01:12:39,729
"This is gonna hurt me
more than it does you,"

1080
01:12:39,730 --> 01:12:42,230
is the customary
way to start off.

1081
01:12:42,240 --> 01:12:46,739
Least ways, that's how
I always got into it.

1082
01:12:46,740 --> 01:12:51,240
<i>You know, I had a hunch
you never listened to me.</i>

1083
01:12:51,250 --> 01:12:53,249
Pa...

1084
01:12:53,250 --> 01:12:57,749
I have tried,
all the years that
you've been with us,

1085
01:12:57,750 --> 01:13:01,250
to make you feel
welcome... wanted.

1086
01:13:01,760 --> 01:13:04,260
And you have been.

1087
01:13:04,760 --> 01:13:10,259
There have been times
when, well, I've overlooked
things that you've done...

1088
01:13:10,260 --> 01:13:14,260
More than I would
for any other member
of the family.

1089
01:13:14,270 --> 01:13:18,280
What kind of things?
But I won't have you making
trouble for Alice and Joe.

1090
01:13:18,281 --> 01:13:20,769
Me cause trouble?

1091
01:13:20,770 --> 01:13:23,770
Joe carder's
making his own trouble;
More than he realizes.

1092
01:13:23,780 --> 01:13:26,790
Thinks just 'cause
he runs that little
no-account newspaper...

1093
01:13:26,791 --> 01:13:29,279
I want you
to promise me one thing:

1094
01:13:29,280 --> 01:13:32,780
That you will never again
argue politics with Joe carder.

1095
01:13:32,790 --> 01:13:34,800
Well, now, it weren't just me.

1096
01:13:34,801 --> 01:13:40,789
Don't you ever say one word
to him about whether Dakota
should be one state or two.

1097
01:13:40,790 --> 01:13:42,790
Suppose he says something first?

1098
01:13:42,800 --> 01:13:47,305
I'm not talking about him,
I'm talking about you.
I'm talkin' about him!

1099
01:13:47,306 --> 01:13:51,800
What do you think I'm gonna do?
Just sit like a ninny and not
say nothin' if he pops off?

1100
01:13:51,810 --> 01:13:55,809
I've said my say.
You've heard me.

1101
01:13:55,810 --> 01:13:58,809
That's the way
it's gonna have to be.

1102
01:13:58,810 --> 01:14:02,810
Now, that's the way it
ain't gonna have to be.
I'll tell you that much.

1103
01:14:02,820 --> 01:14:05,830
If you think I'm gonna
give up my right
of free speech...

1104
01:14:06,320 --> 01:14:08,319
That men fought and died for...

1105
01:14:08,320 --> 01:14:11,820
Just so Joe carder can have
everything his own way...

1106
01:14:11,830 --> 01:14:15,340
Will you listen to me?
<i>You think I'm gonna sit
like a bump on a log...</i>

1107
01:14:15,341 --> 01:14:19,829
Whilst maybe
my own granddaughter
is fixin' to marry some...

1108
01:14:19,830 --> 01:14:24,839
Benedict Arnold!
I'll tell you what I think!

1109
01:14:24,840 --> 01:14:27,839
If you're gonna remain here
as a member of this family,

1110
01:14:27,840 --> 01:14:31,340
then you better
start to exercise
a little self-control...

1111
01:14:31,350 --> 01:14:34,350
Just the same as everybody else!

1112
01:14:39,350 --> 01:14:41,850
You said that.

1113
01:14:41,860 --> 01:14:45,870
If'n I'm gonna stay here?

1114
01:15:00,370 --> 01:15:02,370
Every time i...
hello,
grandpa.

1115
01:15:02,380 --> 01:15:05,879
Hello, grandpa.
Mine is shinier
than yours.

1116
01:15:05,880 --> 01:15:08,879
That has a little
dent on it though.

1117
01:15:08,880 --> 01:15:13,380
<i>[ Children continue chattering ]</i>

1118
01:15:17,890 --> 01:15:20,390
Grandpa, what are you doin'?

1119
01:15:20,890 --> 01:15:23,390
I know when I ain't wanted.

1120
01:15:23,400 --> 01:15:25,410
I don't have to be
hit on the head...

1121
01:15:25,411 --> 01:15:27,399
With a 10-foot pole.

1122
01:15:27,400 --> 01:15:30,399
What are you talking about,
"not wanted"?

1123
01:15:30,400 --> 01:15:33,400
I ain't so old or so feeble
or so hard up that...

